This vulnerability is classified as critical because it can lead to full system compromise, data breaches, and service disruption.

1. Apply Principle of Least Privilege
Run web server with minimal permissions, No root/admin execution, and Restrict file access

2. Use Web Application Firewall (WAF)
A WAF can help block malicious requests:
Detects suspicious patterns, Blocks command injection attempts

3. Use safe APIs or predefined commands, not raw input.
Do NOT pass user input into functions like:
system(), exec(), shell_exec(), passthru()
